atari800
------------------------------------------
Atari800 is the emulator of Atari 8-bit computer systems and 5200 game console
for Unix, Linux, Amiga, MS-DOS, Atari TT/Falcon, MS-Windows, MS WinCE, Sega
Dreamcast, Android and other systems supported by the SDL library. Our main
objective is to create a freely distributable portable emulator (i.e. with
source code available).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libSDL2_2.0_0-2.32.70-1
  libcurl4-8.20.0-1
  libmp3lame0-3.100-1
  libpng16-1.6.47-2
  libreadline8-8.3-1
  zlib0-1.3.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-3
  autoconf-archive-2024.10.16-1
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  libSDL2-devel-2.32.70-1
  libcurl-devel-8.20.0-1
  libmp3lame-devel-3.100-1
  libpng-devel-1.6.47-2
  libreadline-devel-8.3-1
  make-4.4.1-2
  zlib-devel-1.3.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/atari800/atari800

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/atari800/atari800/archive/refs/tags/ATARI800_7_0_0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack atari800-7.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./atari800-7.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/atari800-7.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/atari800-7.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(atari800)
  /usr/bin/atari800.exe
  /usr/bin/cart.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/atari800.README
